means: 把(汽车前灯的)远光调为近光

example.tran: 他们把食物放到调味汁里蘸了蘸。
example.ex: They dip the food into the sauce...

example.tran: 把底部在冷水中快速地浸一下后拿出来。
example.ex: Quickly dip the base in and out of cold water.

example.tran: 往瓶子里蘸一下的量就应该能涂满整个指甲。
example.ex: One dip into the bottle should do an entire nail.

value.def: If you dip something in a liquid, you put it into the liquid for a short time, so that only part of it is covered, and take it out again.

example.tran: 她把手伸进糖果罐，摸出了一颗糖。
example.ex: She dipped a hand into the jar of sweets and pulled one out...

example.tran: 把手伸进锅里时当心你的手指头。
example.ex: Watch your fingers as you dip into the pot...

example.tran: 让孩子们伸手进去摸摸，猜猜每个容器里面是什么。
example.ex: Ask the children to guess what's in each container by dipping their hands in.

value.def: If you dip your hand into a container or dip into the container, you put your hand into it in order to take something out of it.

example.tran: 布莱克很熟练地跳上了船，他的重量使小船微微向下沉了沉。
example.ex: Blake jumped in expertly; the boat dipped slightly under his weight...

example.tran: 太阳落到了地平线下。
example.ex: The sun dipped below the horizon.

example.tran: 我注意到了一些细节：头的往下一沉，肩膀的突然颤动。
example.ex: I noticed little things, a dip of the head, a twitch in the shoulder.

value.def: If something dips, it makes a downward movement, usually quite quickly.
value.tran: (通常指迅速地)下降，下落，下沉

example.tran: 道路陡然沉下去又升上来。
example.ex: The road dipped and rose again.

example.tran: 突然下降进入一条隧道的小路
example.ex: ...a path which suddenly dips down into a tunnel.

example.tran: 在下坡处，向右转。
example.ex: Where the road makes a dip, turn right.

value.def: If an area of land, a road, or a path dips, it goes down quite suddenly to a lower level.
value.tran: 陡然下降;凹下去;突然下倾

example.tran: 他们的父亲在帮忙给羊群洗药浴。
example.ex: Their father was helping to dip the sheep.

value.def: When farmers dip sheep or other farm animals, they put them into a container of liquid with chemicals in it, in order to kill harmful insects which live on the animals' bodies.

example.tran: 他挖土豆并帮忙给羊群洗药浴。
example.ex: He digs potatoes and helps with the sheep dipping.

example.tran: 羊群用的药浴液
example.ex: ...sheep dip.

gramarinfo.label: also N in pl, usu supp N

value.def: Dip is a liquid with chemicals in it which animals or objects can be dipped in to disinfect or clean them.

example.tran: 上个月失业率降到了 6.9%。
example.ex: Unemployment dipped to 6.9 per cent last month...

example.tran: 由于支持率有所下降，总统变得更加谨慎了。
example.ex: The president became more cautious as his popularity dipped.

example.tran: 目前农场开支的减少
example.ex: ...the current dip in farm spending.

value.def: If the amount or level of something dips, it becomes smaller or lower, usually only for a short period of time.
value.tran: (数量或水平，通常短暂地)下降，下跌，减少

example.tran: 或许我们可以只买一点儿蘸酱。
example.ex: Maybe we could just buy some dips.

example.tran: 配鳄梨酱的对虾
example.ex: ...prawns with avocado dip.

value.def: A dip is a thick creamy sauce. You dip pieces of raw vegetable or biscuits into the sauce and then eat them.
value.tran: 蘸酱;(蘸蔬菜或饼干吃的)调味酱，果酱

example.tran: 用在泳池里游一阵后歇一阵的几个空当，她翻完了一本平装本言情小说。
example.ex: She flicked through a romantic paperback between occasional dips in the pool.

value.def: If you have or take a dip, you go for a quick swim in the sea, a river, or a swimming pool.

example.tran: 当他们靠近一辆缓慢行驶的货车时，他把汽车前灯调成了近光。
example.ex: He dipped his headlights as they came up behind a slow-moving van...

example.tran: 这幅图片显示的是从一辆使用正常近光灯的汽车上所看到的景色。
example.ex: This picture shows the view from a car using normal dipped lights.

value.def: If you are driving a car and dip the headlights, you operate a switch that makes them shine downwards, so that they do not shine directly into the eyes of other drivers.

value.boxr_value: in AM, use 美国英语用 dim

example.tran: 博览佛教群书的机会
example.ex: ...a chance to dip into a wide selection of books on Buddhism.

value.def: If you dip into a book, you have a brief look at it without reading or studying it seriously.

example.tran: 正当她准备动用自己的存款时，格雷格赶来给她救了急。
example.ex: Just when she was ready to dip into her savings, Greg hastened to her rescue.

value.def: If you dip into a sum of money that you had intended to save, you use some of it to buy something or pay for something.
